  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity study was conducted informally during model development to evaluate the influence of viscosity and power-law exponent on predicted hemolysis index across the five operating points; results confirmed low parametric sensitivity and supported the MRL 2 classification. This screening activity informed the team's confidence in the model inputs factor rating but was not elevated to a formal structured analysis node in this package.",
