      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs (fluid viscosity, pump geometry, rotational speed, inlet flow profiles) must be characterized with documented uncertainty bounds appropriate for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Fluid viscosity characterized at operating temperature (37°C) with ±2% measurement uncertainty. Pump geometry digitized from FDA benchmark CAD with dimensional tolerance ±0.05 mm. Inlet velocity profiles derived from upstream pipe flow assumption, validated against PIV inlet measurements. An informal screening sensitivity study conducted during model development confirmed that ±5% variation in viscosity and ±10% variation in power-law exponent produced less than 3% change in predicted NIH, supporting the adequacy of the nominal input characterization for MRL 2. Input uncertainty bounds documented in simulation report."
