    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped to Gradation 1 and not formally assessed per MRL 2 requirements. Validation evidence demonstrates NIH prediction within 8.3% MAPE of FDA benchmark experimental data with RH < 1 at all five CPB operating points. Model form, discretization, and software quality all confirmed adequate. The informal screening sensitivity study conducted during model development provided additional confidence in model input adequacy. The credibility evidence package is judged sufficient to support the regulatory decision that the CFD model can reliably identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
